e Connor]] in the British soap opera ''[[Coronation Street]]''\n*Kate Fiztgerald,  main character of novel and film ''[[My Sister's Keeper (novel)|My Sister's Keeper]]'', where she has had [[Acute lymphoblastic leukemia|acute lypmphoblastic leukemia]].\n* [[Bob (Blackadder character)|Kate Ditchburn]], in the TV comedy ''Blackadder II''\n* [[Kate Lockley]], on the TV show ''Angel''\n* Kate Marsh, in the video game [[Life Is Strange]]\n* [[List of Grand Theft Auto IV characters#Kate McReary|Kate McReary]], in the video game ''[[Grand Theft Auto IV]]''\n*[[Kate Mitchell]] in the British soap opera ''[[EastEnders]]''\n* [[Kate Morgan (24 character)|Kate Morgan (''24'' character)]], in the TV series ''24' and the movie ''24: Live Another Day''\n* [[Manhunter (Kate Spencer)]], a DC Comics heroine\n* [[Kate Roberts DiMera]], on the American soap opera ''[[Days of Our Lives]]''.\n* Kate Tomten, the eldest of the Tomten kids in the children's show ''[[Noddy (TV series)|Noddy]]''.\n* Kate from ''[[All Dogs Go to Heaven]]''\n* Kate Connolly from Maggie Stiefvater's \u201cThe Scorpio Races\u201d\n* Kate Takenomiya from Akira Hiramoto's \"Prison School\"\n* Katie Holt from \u201cVoltron - Legendary Defender\u201d\n* Kate Denson from \"Dead by Daylight\" (Videogame) Episode: \"Curtain Call\"\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{given name}}\n<!-- It does not help to add disambig or hndis tags where the page only contains people who share a given name -->\n\n[[Category:English given names]]\n[[Category:Given names of Greek language origin]]\n[[Category:Croatian feminine given names]]\n\n[[hu:Kata (keresztn\u00e9v)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox given name\n| name = Kate\n| image = Carlo Crivelli 014.jpg\n| imagesiz = 200\n| caption = ''[[Catherine of Alexandria]]'', by [[Carlo Crivelli]]\n| pronunciation= \n| gender = Female\n| meaning = ''pure''\n| region = \n| origin =  [[Latin]], [[French language|French]], [[English language|English]], [[Welsh language|Welsh]], [[Irish language|Irish]]\n| related names = [[Katherine (given name)|Katherine]]<br>\nKatharine [[Catherine (disambiguation)|Catherine]]<br>[[Kathryn (name)|Kathryn]]<br>[[Kathleen (given name)|Kathleen]]<br>[[Katarina (given name)|Katarina]]<br>[[Katrina (given name)|Katrina]]<br>Kait<br>[[Caitlin]]<br>[[Caitr\u00edona]]<br>[[Caterina]]<br>[[Cate]]<br>[[Catie]]<br>[[Cathie]]<br>[[Caty]]<br>[[Katie]]<br>[[Katy (given name)|Katy]]<br>[[Katey]]<br>[[Katia]]<br>[[Catia (given name)|Catia]]<br>[[Katia (given name)|Katia]]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n'''Kate''' is a feminine given name. It is a short form of multiple feminine names, most notably [[Katherine]] but also [[Caitlin]] and others.\n\n== Translations and variations ==\n* Arabic: \u0643\u064a\u062a\n* Belarusian: \u041a\u0435\u0439\u0442 (Kiejt)\n* Bengali: \u0995\u09c7\u099f (K\u0113\u1e6da)\n* Bulgarian: \u041a\u0435\u0439\u0442 (Ke\u012dt), Katerina\n* Chinese Simplified: \u51ef\u7279 (K\u01ceit\u00e8)\n* Chinese Traditional: \u51f1\u7279 (K\u01ceit\u00e8)\n* Croatian: Ina, Kata, Katica, Tina\n* Czech: Katka, Kate\u0159ina, Ka\u010dka, K\u00e1\u0165a, Ka\u010denka, K\u00e1\u010da, Ka\u010d\u00ed, Ka\u010dena\n* Danish: Katja, Trine, Caja, Ina, Kaja, Karen, Karin, Karina\n* Dutch: Cato, Ina, Katinka, Katja, Rina, Tina, Trijntje, Karin, Tineke\n* English: Kat, Kathi, Kathie, Kathy, Kay, Kit, Kitty, Kae, Kaye, Katey, Katie, Katy, Kayla, Kaety, Katee, Kaylee, Kayleen, Kaylyn, Kaytie\n* Estonian: Kaisa, Kati, Keit, Riina, Triinu\n* Finnish: Kaija, Kaisa, Kata, Kati, Katri, Riina, Kaarina, Karin\n* Georgian: Eka \n* German: Cathrin, Catrin, Ina, K\u00e4the, Kathrin, Katinka, Katja, Karen, Karin, Karina\n* Greek: \u039a\u03b1\u03af\u03c4\u03b7 (Ka\u00edti\u0331)\n* Gujarati: \u0a95\u0ac7\u0a9f (K\u0113\u1e6da)\n* Hawaiian: Kalena \n* Hebrew: \u05e7\u05d9\u05d9\u05d8\n* Hindi: \u0915\u0947\u091f (K\u0113\u1e6da)\n* Hungarian: Katalin, Kata, Kati, Katalinka, Kat\u00f3, Kitti\n* Irish: C\u00e1it, R\u00edona\n* Italian: Catia, Katia, Rina \n* J