o defeat. Shantae retains her ability to transform into other creatures, now utilized via an ability called \"fusion magic\" that allows her to instantly transform and use a creature's ability without having to select it like in past games. Additional special abilities can be performed by dancing. A new collectible card system allows players to obtain monster cards and use them to augment Shantae's abilities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2019/08/wayforward_reveals_shantae_and_the_seven_sirens_the_half-genie_heros_next_adventure|title=WayForward Reveals Shantae And The Seven Sirens, The Half-Genie Hero's Next Adventure|website=[[Nintendo Life]]|last=Doolan|first=Liam|date=August 14, 2019|accessdate=August 15, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815143149/http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2019/08/wayforward_reveals_shantae_and_the_seven_sirens_the_half-genie_heros_next_adventure|archive-date=August 15, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Like other games in the series, completing the story awards the player with bonus artwork based on their final time and completion percentage, and unlocks a [[New Game Plus]] mode, which gives Shantae all of her transformations from the start of the game, in order to facilitate [[speedrun]]s.\n\n==Plot==\nThe game follows the half-genie Shantae as she and her friends are invited to a tropical island to participate in the Half-Genie Festival. During a performance, the other half-genies in attendance mysteriously disappear, and Shantae must search the island and the sunken city beneath it to find them and uncover the reason for their abduction. Along the way, she runs afoul of her longtime nemesis Risky Boots and the mysterious rulers of this island, the \"Seven Sirens\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendolife.com/news/2020/03/shantae_and_the_seven_sirens_sets_course_for_switch_this_may_new_details_revealed|title=Shantae And The Seven Sirens Sets Course For Switch This May, New Details Revealed|last=Craddock|first=Ryan|date=March 27, 2020||website=[[Nintendo Life]]|accessdate=March 28, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Development==\nOn March 25, 2019, WayForward revealed the game under the working title ''Shantae 5'', and stated it would be released on multiple platforms, including the newly-announced [[Apple Arcade]] service, later that same year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gameinformer.com/2019/03/25/wayforward-announces-shantae-5|title=WayForward Announces Shantae 5|website=[[GameInformer]]|last=Khan|first=Imran|date=March 25, 2019|accessdate=August 15, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815143153/https://www.gameinformer.com/2019/03/25/wayforward-announces-shantae-5|archive-date=August 15, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.destructoid.com/shantae-returns-in-an-all-new-adventure-later-this-year-547731.phtml|title=Shantae returns in an all new adventure later this year|website=[[Destructoid]]|last=Moyse|first=Chris|date=March 25, 2019|accessdate=August 15, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190326043554/https://www.destructoid.com/shantae-returns-in-an-all-new-adventure-later-this-year-547731.phtml|archive-date=March 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The official title and first gameplay details were confirmed the following August.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.destructoid.com/shantae-and-the-seven-sirens-reveals-title-plot-details-and-first-screenshots-563797.phtml|title=Shantae and the Seven Sirens reveals title, plot details and first screenshots|last=Moyse|first=Chris|date=March 25, 2019|website=[[Destructoid]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191125061047/https://www.destructoid.com/shantae-and-the-seven-sirens-reveals-title-plot-details-and-first-screenshots-563797.phtml|archive-date=November 24, 2019|accessdate=August 15, 2019}}</ref> ''Seven Sirens'' features 2D hand-painted artwork designed for [[4K resolution]] devices, along with animated cutscenes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gameinformer.com/2019/08/14/wayforward-reveals-shantae-and-the-seven-sirens|title=WayForward Reveals Shantae And The Seven Sirens|website=[[GameInformer]]|last=Khan|first=Imran|date=August 14, 2019|accessdate=August 15, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815143153/https://www.gameinformer.com/2019/08/14/wayforward-reveals-shantae-and-the-seven-sirens|archive-date=August 15, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The game's opening sequence was animated by [[Studio Trigger]] and features an original song with vocals by Shantae voice actress [[Cristina Vee]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.destructoid.com/check-out-shantae-5-s-wild-opening-anime-right-here-559757.phtml|title=Check out Shantae 5's wild opening anime right here|website=[[Destructoid]]|last=Moyse|first=Chris|date=July 5, 2019|accessdate=August 15, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190727190416/https://www.destructoid.com/check-out-shantae-5-s-wild-opening-anime-right-here-559757.phtml|archive-date=July 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The first part of the game<ref>{{cite tweet|user=WayForward|number=1174452283641344003|title=Join Shantae on an all-new tropical adventure! Shantae and the Seven Sirens Part 1 launches tomorrow @AppleArcade!|date=September 18, 2019|access-date=September 18, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191125061809/https:/twitter.com/WayForward/status/1174452283641344003|archive-date=November 24, 2019|url-status=live|author=}}</ref> was released for iOS on September 19, 2019 as a launch title of the [[Apple Arcade]] subscription service;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2019-09-16-heres-every-game-launching-as-part-of-apple-arcade-this-thursday|title=Here's every game launching as part of Apple Arcade this Thursday|website=[[Eurogamer]]|last=Wales|first=Matt|date=September 16, 2019|accessdate=September 16, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190918020725/https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2019-09-16-heres-every-game-launching-as-part-of-apple-arcade-this-thursday|archive-date=September 18, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> the remainder of the game will be added with a forthcoming update.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.destructoid.com/review-shantae-and-the-seven-sirens-part-1-567290.phtml|title=Review: Shantae and the Seven Sirens Part 1|last=Carter|first=Chris|date=September 22, 2019|website=Destructoid|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191125061539/https://www.destructoid.com/review-shantae-and-the-seven-sirens-part-1-567290.phtml|archive-date=November 24, 2019|access-date=November 24, 2019}}</ref> iPadOS and tvOS versions of the game on Apple Arcade were released on September 30.<ref>{{cite web |title= Apple Arcade press release |url= https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2019/09/apple-arcade-invites-you-to-play-something-extraordinary/ |date= 2019-09-10 |publisher= [[Apple Inc.|Apple]] |language= en |df= mdy-all |access-date= 2019-09-18 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190916185452/https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2019/09/apple-arcade-invites-you-to-play-something-extraordinary/ |archive-date= 2019-09-16 |url-status= live }}</ref> macOS versions of the game on Apple Arcade were released on October 7. The console and PC versions of the game are scheduled for release on May 28, 2020.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=WayForward|number=1205185630587805697|title=Hey, everyone! Development on Shantae and the Seven Sirens for Console/PC (and Apple Arcade Part 2) is nearly finished! We've moved the release window to Spring 2020, but promise it will be worth the wait! Thank you for your support!|date=December 12, 2019|access-date=December 12, 2019}}</ref> The Part 2 update for the Apple Arcade versions was released on March 28, 2020.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Shantae series}}\n{{Studio Trigger}}\n\n[[Category:2019 video games]]\n[[Category:iOS games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch eShop games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch games]]\n[[Category:Platform games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation Network games]]\n[[Category:Shantae|And the Seven Sirens]]\n[[Category:Fiction about shapeshifting]]\n[[Category:Video games about pirates]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in the United States]]\n[[Category:Video games featuring female protagonists]]\n[[Category:Video games featuring female antagonists]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n[[Category:Xbox One games]]\n[[Category:Apple Arcade games]]\n", "name_user": "181.166.24.129", "label": "vandal", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shantae_and_the_Seven_Sirens"}
